==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sycophancy
<hw>Syc"o*phan*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. L.
<ets>sycophantia</ets> deceit, Gr. <?/ false accusation.]</ety> <def>The
character or characteristic of a sycophant.</def> Hence: -⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(a)</sd> <def>False accusation; calumniation; talebearing.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bp. Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(b)</sd> <def>Obsequious flattery; servility.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>sycophancy</qex> of A.Philips had prejudiced Mr. Addison
against Pope.</q> <rj><qau>Bp. Warburton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sycophant</ent>⟦br⟧
